<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hole" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hole,</orth> 1) a hollow place, a cavity: <bibl n="shak. luc 1175" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1175</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 3, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 143</bibl>; cf. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.88" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.734" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 734</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.159" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.159" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 159</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 2, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.165" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 165</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.29" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.237" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 237</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 17</bibl>. Used of wounds: <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.165" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 165</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.125" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 125</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.2.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 2, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 1, 31</bibl>.<lb />2) a pit: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.120" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.287" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 287</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 129</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 129</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 129</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 129</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 129</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.104" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.205" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 205</bibl>.
<lb />3) any hiding and lurking place: <cit><quote>the earth had not a h. to hide this deed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.36" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 36</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>darts his light through every guilty h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 43</bibl></cit>. Obscenely: <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 97</bibl>.
<lb />4) the small entrance where mice pass: <emph>the mouse's h.</emph> Per. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.0." default="NO" valid="yes">III Prol. 6</bibl>.
<lb />5) the hollow of the palm: <cit><quote>spit in the h. and tune again,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 1, 40</bibl></cit> (== spit in your hand, take courage and make a new effort).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>